India will soon launch in stages its first bullet train, whose total journey of 508 kilometers is expected to be completed by 2024.The fast rail project is likely to operate in a first phase along a 325-kilometer stretch between the cities of Ahmedabad and Vapi, both cities in the Indian state of Gujarat, in the west of the country. The reason for this strategy is related to the issue of land acquisition andthe problems associated with it, the Daily News and Analysis newspaper reported. Recently, the Japanese Embassy in India shared some photos of the E5 Shinkansen, which will be modified for use as a high-speed rail line between the cities of Mumbai, the country’s financial and commercial capital, and Ahmedabad, India’s important economic and industrial center. After the completion of this project, the distance between Mumbai and Ahmedabad will be completed in only two hours. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The cornerstone of this initiative was laid in Ahmedabad in September 2017 by Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi and his then Japanese counterpart, Shinzo Abe. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION